com.panviva.util.pgc.rule

Class MatchProperties

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.panviva.util.pgc.rule.MatchProperties
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IMatchProperties
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PartitionTargetProperties

    public class MatchProperties
extends java.lang.Object
implements IMatchProperties
    Implementation class of the IMatchProperties interface. This class is used to provide conditional matching for source and target path tasks. The match element is defined as a child of the task element in the rules.xml rules template file. Many of the capabilities of this class can be performed using XPATH conditional notation. However the replacement capability is unique to this class.
    Author:
    jcharles
